          </div><div class="txt commenttxt">&nbsp;If you start with a clean shower, it works pretty well. &nbsp;If you start with a not so clean shower, it takes time to work well. &nbsp;If you start with a gross shower, forget it. &nbsp;Get some gloves, some abrasive cleanser, and a sponge with a scrubbing pad and clean it yourself. &nbsp;THEN use the sprayer.<br> <br> I have not yet tried dollar store or other alternative chemicals in the sprayer yet. &nbsp;It seems that the ideal mod here is to permanently install some sort of tank with a wide-mouthed screw-top opening that is easily filled.<br></div><div id="files"><a name="files"></a></div><div id="commentactioncontainer_C8J4IZ3G7DYYNN7" class="comment-actions"><div class="commentloop_div_4"><div><a id="replytolink_C8J4IZ3G7DYYNN7" class="bright replylink commentloop_a_5" href="#" onclick="return false;"><b>REPLY</b></a></div></div></div></div><a name="CL2NUQ6FHM8QZR3"></a><div class="comment entryList clearfix  " style="margin-left:10px;"><div class="comment-authorpic"><a href="/member/pamelahowell/"><img src="/static/defaultIMG/user.TINY.gif" alt="" /></a></div><div class="comment-info"><span>Jun 19, 2008. 5:38 AM</span><a href="/member/pamelahowell/" class="entryListTitle" style="line-height:16px;padding-right:4px;padding-left:0px;">pamelahowell</a>
